00:14:03.660 --> 00:14:05.270
frameworks.

00:14:05.270 --> 00:14:08.450
Probably many people know that
here in Brazil we are in a

00:14:08.450 --> 00:14:10.120
very important moment.

00:14:10.120 --> 00:14:13.890
We have a regulation that
has been developed in a

00:14:13.890 --> 00:14:16.680
collaborative way online.

00:14:16.680 --> 00:14:19.840
All the people that use the
internet and been able to make

00:14:19.840 --> 00:14:21.640
comments to this regulation.

00:14:21.640 --> 00:14:24.870
And after this collaborative
process that lasted for three

00:14:24.870 --> 00:14:28.520
months, this regulation has
been sent to Congress.

00:14:28.520 --> 00:14:30.900
And now it's being
on the revision.

00:14:30.900 --> 00:14:34.855
And because ITU happened at the
same time that this law

00:14:34.855 --> 00:14:39.520
arrived in congress, WCIT had
a negative impact on the

00:14:39.520 --> 00:14:42.220
discussion of his view bill,
because this bill tries to

00:14:42.220 --> 00:14:46.840
enable network neutrality, which
would be fundamental to

00:14:46.840 --> 00:14:50.350
the guarantee of innovation
in Brazil.

00:14:50.350 --> 00:14:52.680
Because the discussion is taking
place in WCIT right

00:14:52.680 --> 00:14:56.290
now, the discussions in Congress
have been stalled,

00:14:56.290 --> 00:14:58.730
because our government doesn't
have a position on network

00:14:58.730 --> 00:14:59.540
neutrality.

00:14:59.540 --> 00:15:04.280
And they wanted to go to WCIT
and hear from other countries,

00:15:04.280 --> 00:15:07.060
what are their perspectives,
hear from [INAUDIBLE] what is

00:15:07.060 --> 00:15:07.980
their perspective.

00:15:07.980 --> 00:15:11.200
So I think that developing
countries that do not have

00:15:11.200 --> 00:15:15.710
this regulatory framework in
place as developed countries

00:15:15.710 --> 00:15:19.030
already have, this may have
a negative impact.

00:15:19.030 --> 00:15:22.260
But it also creates an
opportunity for us to be aware

00:15:22.260 --> 00:15:25.970
of how there is an interplay
between international

00:15:25.970 --> 00:15:30.820
regulation and national
regulation as well.

00:15:30.820 --> 00:15:32.730
DEREK SLATER: Claudio, I want
to turn you on that point,

00:15:32.730 --> 00:15:37.930
because is that a comparable
experience to what you've had

00:15:37.930 --> 00:15:39.140
with your organization?

00:15:39.140 --> 00:15:41.700
Or what are the key differences
with what Marilia

00:15:41.700 --> 00:15:42.950
has been discussing.

00:15:45.580 --> 00:15:49.540
CLAUDIO RUIZ: I think what
Marilia has pointed out, it's

00:15:49.540 --> 00:15:50.540
pretty important.

00:15:50.540 --> 00:15:56.620
It's the key discussion in all
this thing, especially because

00:15:56.620 --> 00:15:58.265
this [INAUDIBLE]

00:15:58.265 --> 00:16:01.370
the WCIT discussion has
been closed doors.

00:16:01.370 --> 00:16:04.220
