either one idea what is

00:16:35.860 --> 00:16:37.820
happening, and neither
is the other.

00:16:37.820 --> 00:16:41.180
I would say all the discussion
on WCIT, and all the

00:16:41.180 --> 00:16:44.370
discussion about what we're
talking about, it's

00:16:44.370 --> 00:16:45.540
just about the power.

00:16:45.540 --> 00:16:48.300
And it's just about controlling
things.

00:16:48.300 --> 00:16:52.570
And it's more about
a controlling

00:16:52.570 --> 00:16:54.130
structure in some way.

00:16:54.130 --> 00:16:58.090
So my point here, and experience
that we have here

00:16:58.090 --> 00:17:03.710
in Chile, I would say, is just
to try to use this opportunity

00:17:03.710 --> 00:17:08.300
and to use this momentum, this
discussion momentum worldwide

00:17:08.300 --> 00:17:10.300
international agenda.

00:17:10.300 --> 00:17:14.150
And one of the things that at
least here in Chile we have

00:17:14.150 --> 00:17:19.079
faced, it's in spite of the fact
that or government has

00:17:19.079 --> 00:17:26.869
this digital agenda, digital
plan for the next 10 years,

00:17:26.869 --> 00:17:30.770
and we don't have a very clear
idea about and what is the

00:17:30.770 --> 00:17:36.020
Chilean position on WCIT, and
why our government is not

00:17:36.020 --> 00:17:40.530
opening up the doors to other
civil society organizations or

00:17:40.530 --> 00:17:45.610
different multi-stakeholders
and groups to just share

00:17:45.610 --> 00:17:51.430
opinions and actually adding
some different points to the

00:17:51.430 --> 00:17:52.260
Chilean position.

00:17:52.260 --> 00:17:54.810
So I think it's pretty important
what Marilia said

00:17:54.810 --> 00:17:59.640
about how this WCIT discussion
worldwide can be useful on the

00:17:59.640 --> 00:18:03.070
national level or even in the
regional level, to just

00:18:03.070 --> 00:18:07.480
empower different stakeholders,
[INAUDIBLE]

00:18:07.480 --> 00:18:10.040
structures to taking
decisions.

00:18:10.040 --> 00:18:17.560
And using multi-stakeholders
and groups to discuss the

00:18:17.560 --> 00:18:21.020
internet in general, not just
in a technical way, or not

00:18:21.020 --> 00:18:24.330
just in a political way, but
taking talking about the

00:18:24.330 --> 00:18:28.250
internet as a platform to
developing human rights.

00:18:28.250 --> 00:18:31.290
And when we're talking about
human rights, we need to

00:18:31.290 --> 00:18:34.820
address all the perspectives
which are involved in those

00:18:34.820 --> 00:18:37.420
things, and not just the
government's point of view, or

00:18:37.420 --> 00:18:39.740
not just the company's agenda.

00:18:39.740 --> 00:18:43.100
So I think that these things, it
would be very interesting.

00:18:43.100 --> 00:18:47.500
And I'm pretty concerned about
the way the discussion would

00:18:47.500 --> 00:18:50.370
be framed in the future,
taking into account the

00:18:50.370 --> 00:18:53.410
importance of the discussion
and taking especially into

00:18:53.410 --> 00:18:58.740
account all the media attendance
that is now into

00:18:58.740 --> 00:19:01.940
Dubai, and especially in
these human rights

00:19:01.940 --> 00:19:02.960
groups around the world.

00:19:02.960 --> 00:19:05.620
I think that it would be
very, very important.

00:19:05.620 --> 00:19:08.970
DEREK SLATER: And Mawaki, one
of things that both Marilia

00:19:08.970 --> 00:19:12.500
and Claudio spoke to as sort
of, this is an important

00:19:12.500 --> 00:19:16.290
moment, not just what happens
at the WCIT today, but as a

00:19:16.290 --> 00:19:18.870
moment of growing the community
of people who are

00:19:18.870 --> 00:19:20.190
thinking about these issues.

