or less aware of it.

00:19:54.020 --> 00:19:58.740
I have to admit that not many
people were involved in the

00:19:58.740 --> 00:20:02.950
process at that time, especially
in the side of

00:20:02.950 --> 00:20:05.050
African civil society.

00:20:05.050 --> 00:20:13.200
And WSIS was a tremendous
opportunity for engagement

00:20:13.200 --> 00:20:16.040
around the world, particularly
in Africa.

00:20:16.040 --> 00:20:19.750
People have become aware of
internet governance issues and

00:20:19.750 --> 00:20:24.710
challenges more acutely since
WSIS, since the preparatory

00:20:24.710 --> 00:20:27.410
process in 2003.

00:20:27.410 --> 00:20:33.970
And APC has been, of course,
advocating around those issues

00:20:33.970 --> 00:20:35.850
since then.

00:20:35.850 --> 00:20:41.530
In general, even before the
particular issue area of

00:20:41.530 --> 00:20:46.450
internet governance, APC has
always been advocating for

00:20:46.450 --> 00:20:50.630
more affordable access
to ICTs and inclusive

00:20:50.630 --> 00:20:52.460
policy-making processes.

00:20:52.460 --> 00:20:55.140
So with the WSIS, the
internet Governance

00:20:55.140 --> 00:20:57.610
issues came to the fore.

00:20:57.610 --> 00:21:04.390
Now as we progress, since 2002,
since the WSIS, the

00:21:04.390 --> 00:21:09.570
ranks of civil society folks
involved in Africa have been

00:21:09.570 --> 00:21:14.640
growing, the main challenge
always being capacity to

00:21:14.640 --> 00:21:17.840
building and funding
to participate in

00:21:17.840 --> 00:21:22.130
meetings around the world.

00:21:22.130 --> 00:21:27.070
