be part of the ITR.

00:36:04.480 --> 00:36:08.270
And so the definition debate
has been about--

00:36:08.270 --> 00:36:10.210
I think the US--

00:36:10.210 --> 00:36:12.700
people are finding out about
that debate in the US.

00:36:12.700 --> 00:36:16.760
That has been a long-running
debate, whether internet is

00:36:16.760 --> 00:36:21.150
part of basic telecommunications
or it's

00:36:21.150 --> 00:36:26.170
what you call here enhanced
service, and whether the

00:36:26.170 --> 00:36:29.050
telecom regulatory framework
applied to the internet.

00:36:29.050 --> 00:36:33.410
So once you understand that and
you understand that the

00:36:33.410 --> 00:36:36.610
telecom regulatory framework
cannot apply to the internet,

00:36:36.610 --> 00:36:41.000
because of all the content
issues, for example, that you

00:36:41.000 --> 00:36:43.670
mentioned, Jochai.

00:36:43.670 --> 00:36:51.390
So then the human right
issue does not

00:36:51.390 --> 00:36:52.500
even become a problem.

00:36:52.500 --> 00:36:55.920
Because first of all, to
ITU is part of the UN.

00:36:55.920 --> 00:37:02.150
And there's a clear universal
human rights regime at the UN

00:37:02.150 --> 00:37:04.180
organization level,
across the system.

00:37:04.180 --> 00:37:10.990
So those proposals going against
freedom of expression

00:37:10.990 --> 00:37:16.810
and all that have to be opposed
up front, on the basis

00:37:16.810 --> 00:37:21.380
of the human rights regime
that's accepted and is

00:37:21.380 --> 00:37:23.760
supposed to be enforced at
the level of the UN.

00:37:23.760 --> 00:37:27.680
So at APC, we don't think we
need to include the human

00:37:27.680 --> 00:37:30.320
rights issue within the ITR.

00:37:30.320 --> 00:37:33.035
Those are issues to be debated,
but not within the

00:37:33.035 --> 00:37:36.455
ITR, because the ITRs must be
about basic telecommunicaion

00:37:36.455 --> 00:37:38.340
regulatory framework.

00:37:38.340 --> 00:37:43.480
So as to the question, where
or how to approach those

00:37:43.480 --> 00:37:47.170
issues related to internet,
we have had the Internet

00:37:47.170 --> 00:37:48.560
Governance Forum.

00:37:48.560 --> 00:37:51.890
The problem is-- which is
multi-stakeholder, everybody's

00:37:51.890 --> 00:37:56.170
welcome, civil societies,
governments, and businesses,

00:37:56.170 --> 00:37:57.190
[INAUDIBLE]

00:37:57.190 --> 00:37:58.070
everybody.

00:37:58.070 --> 00:38:02.610
